The link rarely exceeded 90% capacity (10 minutes total), with one brief peak surpassing 100 Mbps. These are isolated bursts, not sustained congestion. While such spikes could cause temporary slowdowns, overall service quality remains excellent, with 99.98% of time within acceptable limits.

**Conclusion**
The link is significantly over-provisioned; consider reducing capacity to optimize costs.
